the copyist having mistaken *a*p for *az*, and substituted the Zvâri*s*
equivalent min for the latter which he supposed was a separate word.

<span id="fn_314"></span>[130:1](sbe37041.htm#fr_316.md) Or 'abstracting.'

<span id="fn_315"></span>[130:2](sbe37041.htm#fr_317.md) See Chaps. XVII,
6, XXXVII, II.

<span id="fn_316"></span>[130:3](sbe37041.htm#fr_318.md) Two brothers who
were contemporaries of Zaratû*s*t. Frashô*s*tar was his father-in-law,
and *G*âmâsp was prime minister of king Vi*s*tâsp.

